cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the error probability of cooperative spectrum sensing, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies cognitive radio networks and the transmission of energy statistics from secondary users to a fusion center. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security issues related to cooperative spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss system-level optimization of cooperative spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve the use of multimedia data (energy statistics) in cooperative spectrum sensing.
